The political institutions, even if they were formally established correctly, remain only a sham behind which patriarchal tribal relations will continue to grow.
The balance of interests between the different ethnic groups is unusually complicated, especially because of the ambiguity of the circumstances, which further complicates the influence of Pakistan and Iran.
The creation of a 'state capable of action', which is the minimalist aim of the whole operation, is also very unrealistic.
