The Spanish are the worst paid according to the data available to Trovit through its search engines in the UK and France.
A British programmer receives an annual gross salary of 45,226 euros and a Frenchman 31,059 euros, compared with the 24,000 euros earned by a Spaniard.
Accordingly, a truck driver has an annual net income of EUR 34,247 in England, EUR 25,751 in France and EUR 16,420 in Spain.
According to Trovit, the lowest paid job in Spain is that of a waiter with a net annual income of €11,592; followed by the job of a salesman with €14,725 and that of a worker with €15,667.
