New vehicle evaluation programmes
In these days of storms and accidents, it is not only the automotive factories that earn
Every day, thousands of vehicles involved in an accident are towed to the workshops, where an assessor must assess the damage and repair costs.
No accident is the same and calculating the cost of parts and working hours can be a lengthy and complicated task.
The calculation of repair costs of between EUR 20 000 and EUR 30 000 per hand, including parts and working hours, can take up to two or three hours.
On the contrary, with the help of the latest computer tools, it is only a matter of minutes.
That is why almost 100% of the experts use these types of systems.
Accident assessment and repair service and application providers shall collect the information they receive from manufacturers for subsequent processing and provide it to their customers in the form of a useful programme.
In Spain, Audatex, part of the American Solera Group, is the market leader; 80% of all reviews are produced with its products.
The other two companies competing in the tool market for assessment and reporting are GtMotive and Eurotax.
Working with the data provided by manufacturers is anything but simple.
According to Eduardo Velázquez, Audatex's sales manager, 63 manufacturers and importers are cooperating, each providing the information in a different format.
In addition, the amount of data to be processed is increasing, to the point that in the last five years more versions, variants and motorizations have been released than in all the previous 15 years.
As soon as a new car comes on the market, the business begins to work.
It is a laborious task, because each of the thousands of vehicle parts must be catalogued and priced.
In addition, each model creates a "smart" graphic image that lets you "click" on different parts of the vehicle.
If the model is a sold-out model, the work can be completed in a week if the process is carried out quickly.
In the case of a less used car, it may take up to three or four months.
For example, in the more exclusive models, they have information on Porsche models but not on Ferrari or Lamborghini.
The number of vehicles on the straits is over 99%.
For the purpose of documentation and database production, Audatex has eight centres worldwide (Spain, France, Germany, USA, Brazil, Mexico, China and Japan) and each of them specializes in a particular brand.
The national headquarters are in Alcobendas (Madrid).
There are more than a hundred technicians (usually mechanics specialists) working simultaneously with three computer screens.
Audatex invests EUR 90 million annually in the development of these databases.
They're recording 2.5 million data every month, and their customers get the updates every other day.
The development of this huge flow of information allows companies to use it in different ways and thus offer different products.
The most common use is for repairs and repairs, but depending on the country, there are also tools for managing scrap or calculating the fault or residual value of a car.
The only company that has a guide to inform about the value of used cars in Spain is Eurotax.
Audatex does not offer this service in Spain, but in the United States.
Audatex's products are easy to see and understand the support it provides to industry experts.
This company offers ten different tools, the star of which is AudaPlus, a standard solution for accident prevention for the evaluators.
It includes vehicles, motorcycles and light and heavy industrial vehicles.
In addition to the cost of the parts, it contains the manufacturer's estimated repair times or paint prices.
This tool is paid for by use, i.e. for each opinion.
The most expensive is for customers who use it rarely, up to ten times a month, i.e. 5.75 euros a month.
In contrast, every insurance company that produces thousands of reviews negotiates the price with Audatex.
Other products, such as AudaVIN, allow a vehicle and the equipment it was running on from the assembly line to be fully identified by the driver's license plate number alone.
AudaGlass is involved in vehicle discs and AudaSubastas is an internet service open to the specialist market for vehicles declared to be totally damaged.
